  "prompt": "What's Home Depot's return/exchange policy?",
  "response": "Home Depot's return policy generally allows customers to return most new, unopened items within 90 days of purchase, provided you have the original receipt. For purchases made with a Home Depot Consumer Credit Card, Commercial Revolving Charge, or Commercial Account, you might qualify for an extended return period of up to 365 days from the date of purchase. \n\nItems like furniture, area rugs, gas-powered equipment, and tractors may have different return policies, often requiring returns within 30 days. Some exceptions and conditions apply to items such as major appliances, which should be inspected upon delivery and can only be returned if they are found to be defective or damaged.\n\nFor online purchases, items can typically be returned in-store or mailed back, though certain restrictions might apply.\n\nAlways check for the latest updates or specific terms on Home Depot's website or contact their customer service for the most accurate information.",
